{"id": "EUVD-2025-124922", "enisaUuid": "386d60d9-d496-36d3-bfd8-b5edbe22cefa", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmailbox: zynqmp-ipi: Fix SGI cleanup on unbind\n\nThe driver incorrectly determines SGI vs SPI interrupts by checking IRQ\nnumber < 16, which fails with dynamic IRQ allocation. During unbind,\nthis causes improper SGI cleanup leading to kernel crash.\n\nAdd explicit irq_type field to pdata for reliable identification of SGI\ninterrupts (type-2) and only clean up SGI resources when appropriate.", "datePublished": "2025-11-12T10:24:36", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-01T06:19:13", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1ee147efee68be00203b1fee6479911debb1edb2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/32bf7c6e01f5ba17a53ba236a770bd0274cefdf4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bb160e791ab15b89188a7a19589b8e11f681bef3", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40161"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40161"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "3b19173c-7ea6-3fb5-8bc4-841f6c2903ce", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "3c2ba1f4-2bca-36d3-856c-4ddd630074e3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.10"}, {"id": "7b79420e-2043-32f5-886b-aa50d05c2d15", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6ffb1635341bec50fa9540ae7827d1e5d75ae0b0 <bb160e791ab15b89188a7a19589b8e11f681bef3"}, {"id": "98e84310-44ac-3afe-b03d-7e5e0e391ac2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18"}, {"id": "a2b1b2b6-7701-36ba-9383-581bb1878b6d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6ffb1635341bec50fa9540ae7827d1e5d75ae0b0 <32bf7c6e01f5ba17a53ba236a770bd0274cefdf4"}, {"id": "a7f71b43-1311-3745-bf2c-25d9ef5da47a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.54"}, {"id": "b2e22576-8603-33b0-8e37-1aa712ed29a6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18-rc1"}, {"id": "c7e986a3-f37f-33d6-a3d1-506